  "bio": "<p>Josue is 17 and has faced many challenges. He survived TB meningitis as a baby and has cerebral palsy, needing hospital-level care at home. Josue cannot sit up, does not speak, and uses a feeding tube. He spends most days in the same room due to his medical needs.</p><p>Josue’s mother, a caring single parent, supports him every day as his caregiver and comfort. She rarely leaves his side and sleeps in his room to help him whenever needed.</p><p>With the help of Artisan Design Studio and the generous support of our donors and community partners, including Lead Coverage, Sunshine on a Ranney Day is excited to provide Josue with a dream bedroom makeover to brighten his days and also create a calming environment for his mother at the end of the day. This project would not be possible without our supporters, whose kindness and contributions truly make a difference for families like Josue’s.</p><p>We cannot wait for them to see their room on Tuesday, May 15, at 5:00 p.m. Join us on Facebook Live for this special moment!</p>",
